Package: CFSTRenD
Type: Package
Title: a comprehensive toolkit for data processing, quality assessment and statistical analysis with tree-ring data
Version: 0.8.0
Author: Xiao Jing Guo
Maintainer: The package maintainer <xiaojing.guo@NRCan-RNCan.gc.ca>
Description: CFSTRenD R package is aimed at streamlining the processing and analysis of tree-ring data. Key features include: 1) manipulation and summarization of tree-ring data; 2) data quality identification and classification; and 3) a flexible detrending and climate-growthmodel based on generalized additive mixed models (GAMM); 4) model selection tool based on Akaike Information Criterion (AIC). Additionally, the package supports generating multiple plots for visual inspection and handles .rwl format files, offering a comprehensive toolkit for CFS-TRenD community and dendrochronologists.
License: GPL-3 
